Descriptive notes . A description of this species was given by Sharp (1882) (as
M. giganteus
). Here we provide photos of the habitus ( Figs 1B, E , 2B ) and focus on morphological characters of the male in different views ( Figs 8 A–C).The median lobe with both parameres is figured in ventral view ( Fig. 5A ), the tip of the median lobe in lateral view ( Fig. 5B ), and the median lobe in ventro-apical view ( Fig. 5C ).
